Name: Access Control List Data
Description: Information needed to enable selective restriction of access to places, systems, or other resources. Includes information pertaining to user groups and roles.

Name: Cost Centre Data
Description: An organisation unit that represents an accounting unit within an HSBC Entity.

Name: Credit Mitigant Data
Description: An account that mitigates credit risk exposure.

Name: Accounting Entry Data
Description: A numerical representation of the net increases and decreases in an account at a specific point in time.

Name: Activity and Audit Log Data
Description: A security-relevant chronological record, set of records, and/or destination and source of records that provide documentary evidence of the sequence of activities that have affected at any time a specific operation, procedure, or event.

Name: Address Data
Description: A location for sending and receiving tangible items or information.

Name: Alert Data
Description: An event that indicates there is a potential problem that should be investigated.

Name: Arrangement Data
Description: A written mutual agreement, enforceable by law, between two or more parties that something shall be done by one or both parties.

Name: Assessment Data
Description: A business activity which identifies a task or tasks which provide information for the evaluation of a given set of criteria.

Name: ATM Data
Description: A branch or outlet that allows customers to complete basic transactions without the aid of Bank teller.

Name: Bank Notes and Bullion Data
Description: Financial inventory information including amount and location of corporate notes and bullion.

Name: Benchmark Data
Description: Standard, or a set of standards, used as a point of reference for evaluating performance of HSBC Products and services.

Name: Benefit Data
Description: An advantage like medical insurance, sick leave, life insurance given to workers or employees or customers.

Name: Biometric Profile Data
Description: Information that identifies an individual based on physical or behavioural traits, examples of which are fingerprints, eye/retina patterns, voice patterns, facial structure/patterns, body movement, and gait.

Name: Branch Data
Description: A legally dependent part of a business organisation or company which acts as a place of business, responsible for the delivery of the products and services of said organisation. It is typically focussed on a particular geographic or jurisdictional locality.

Name: Brand Data
Description: Unique design, sign, symbol, words, or a combination of these, employed in creating an image that identifies a product and differentiates it from its competitors.

Name: Budget Data
Description: A budget is a financial plan for a defined period, often one year. It includes planned volume of products and services, costs and expenses, assets, liabilities and cash flows.

Name: Business Direction Data
Description: An expression of HSBC's intent with regard to the manner and environments in which it wishes to carry out its business.

Name: Business Model Data
Description: Information describing the organisational and management structure of HSBC, examples of which are business and functional hierarchies, legal entities and geographic scope, product and services provided in each geographical area.

Name: Business Plan Data
Description: Information describing the strategy and goal of HSBC.

Name: Business Policy Data
Description: HSBC guidelines to govern its actions. They define the limits within which decisions must be made. HSBC policy also deals with acquisition of resources with which organisational goals can be achieved.

Name: Business Strategy Data
Description: A business strategy is a set of competitive moves and actions that HSBC uses to better serve customers, compete successfully, strengthening performance, and achieve organisational goals. It outlines how business should be carried out to reach the desired ends.

Name: Business Trip Data
Description: A business event that is a journey made by a worker to a place for work purposes, typically one involving some distance.

Name: Case Data
Description: The record of communications, investigations and outcomes pertaining to a specific event impacting the relationship between HSBC and contractors.

Name: Channel Data
Description: A delivery and communication mechanism through which products and services are made available to a customer and by which HSBC and customers communicate with each other.

Name: Claim Data
Description: A request for payment under the terms and conditions of a contract.

Name: Communication Data
Description: Information in relation to an event at which there is an exchange of information with individuals or organisations of interest to HSBC.

Name: Compensation and Payroll Data
Description: Payroll typically involves payments of regular salary and wages, commissions and bonuses. Compensation is broader than pay as it includes all of the benefits and perks that companies provide to employees on top of income

Name: Compliance Risk Rating Data
Description: A measurement scale of accreditation created based on assessment of compliance risks as mandated by Global or regional compliance risk policy.

Name: Compliance Violation Data
Description: An event where an action that does not conform with the 1) compliance policy, 2) operating procedure, or 3) compliance and regulatory laws with in the scope of a either global or regional compliance policy occurs.

Name: Condition Data
Description: Each party in a contract is obligated, or required, to perform a duty under the contract. The contract conditions determine the parties' obligations. A condition is an act or event that affects a party's contractual duty. It is a qualification that is placed on an obligation.

Name: Connected Party Data
Description: A role assumed by a given individual or organisation, with respect to another individual or organisation, that grants it the power to direct or influence the activities of the customer through its management or ownership structure; or who is a beneficial owner of the customer.

Name: Contact Data
Description: A communication with someone, typically in order to give or receive information.

Name: Contract Cash Flow Schedule Data
Description: A cash flow condition that specifies timing and frequency of payments for contracts.

Name: Contract Data
Description: A potential or actual agreement between two or more parties, that provides and affirms the rules and obligations associated with the exchange for value of goods, services and/or resources.

Name: Contract Limit Data
Description: A condition that is applied to a financial value associated with a contract.

Name: Contract Repricing Schedule Data
Description: A repricing schedule changes in initial contract based on various conditions of agreement. Conditions like contract period end, changes in economical conditions, changes in infrastructure and securitisation.

Name: Control Data
Description: Information pertaining to a mechanism or condition that is put in place to govern and manage the conduct of HSBC business. This includes the identifying, recording and assessing performance of HSBC products and services, employee access   and guide on roles and responsibilities.

Name: Account Financial Data
Description: The financial data that is associated to an account. E.g. transactions made into/out of an account. The position (current balance) of the account.

Name: Counterparty Data
Description: A trade party role that is a party with whom HSBC makes a trade or transaction.

Name: Credit Facility Data
Description: A financial instrument that is either an agreement to directly extend credit to a customer by means of one or more credit instruments, or to control the credit risk exposure arising from trading and investment activities.

Name: Credit Hierarchy Data
Description: A Credit Risk Hierarchy is a system of organising a set of credit risk exposures so that the relationships and dependencies between different entities are more intuitive and transparent.

Name: Credit Instrument Data
Description: A financial instrument in which an HSBC entity puts its assets at risk, for a fee, for the benefit of its customer's use

Name: Customer Account Data
Description: An account that is ruled by a product or service agreement between an HSBC legal entity and one or more customer parties.

Name: Exposure Data
Description: The measure of potential future loss resulting from a specific activity or event.

Name: Customer Data
Description: An individual or organisation that is a named party in at least one contract with an HSBC legal entity for a product or service provided by HSBC.

Name: Customer Profile Data
Description: Information pertaining to the delivery and service channels, financial information, biography (such as employment and financial history), anticipated transactional behaviour, social interactions, non-demographic segmentation and lifecycle of an individual or organisation.

Name: Customer Service Data
Description: The assistance and advice provided by a company to those people who buy or use its products or services.

Name: Demographic Profile Data
Description: The identity of an individual based on social or human population characteristics such as age, race, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, and disability.

Name: Deposit Instrument Data
Description: Monetary contracts between HSBC and depositor. They can be created, traded, modified and settled.

Name: Descriptor Data
Description: A multi-valued or complex characteristic that describes something. Includes high level concepts around Descriptor, Measure, Date, etc.

Name: Digital Data
Description: Information in relation to the online presence of an individual or organisation covering content publication, social media, e-commerce and subscriptions, including but not limited to websites blogs, news feeds, forums, messaging, web cast, online shopping, online sales and marketing, online gaming, and streaming services.

Name: Document Data
Description: A piece of written, printed, or electronic matter that provides information or evidence or that serves as an official record.

Name: Economic / Industry Data
Description: Information used to calculate or measure the amount of capital, calculated internally, that an entity needs to support its risks.

Name: Economic Resource Data
Description: Any value item, either tangible or intangible, that is owned, managed, used by, or of specific interest to HSBC in pursuit and accomplishment of its business.

Name: Event Data
Description: An occurrence about which HSBC wishes to keep information as a part of carrying out its mission and conducting its business.

Name: Exchange Rate Data
Description: Exchange rate is the price of one currency in terms of another currency. Exchange rates can be either fixed or floating. Fixed exchange rates are decided by central banks of a country whereas floating exchange rates are decided by the mechanism of market demand and supply.

Name: Financial Position Data
Description: The status of the assets, liabilities, and owners' equity (and their interrelationships) of an organisation, as reflected in its financial statements. Also called financial condition.

Name: External Event Data
Description:
An event which may either increase or decrease HSBC business based on its nature:
    - Economic crises
    - Change in Government rules and law

Name: External Financial Statement Data
Description: They are written records of a business's financial situation. They include standard reports like the balance sheet, income or profit and loss statements, and cash flow statement.

Name: Financial Crime Risk Alert Data
Description: A notification of a financial crime threat. Includes screening and anti money laundering alerts.

Name: Financial Crime Screening Data
Description: Sanctions lists, and information in relation to assessment of entities (individuals, organisations or countries) against those sanctions lists.

Name: Financial Data
Description: An event that changes the HSBC or Financial Institution's financial position.

Name: Financial Instrument Data
Description: Monetary contracts between HSBC and customers. They can be created, traded, modified and settled. They can be cash (currency), evidence of an ownership interest in an entity (share), or a contractual right to receive or deliver cash (bond).

Name: Financial Market Data
Description: A price and trade-related data for financial instrument reports by a trading venue such as a stock exchange.

Name: Financial Statement Data
Description: A balance sheet or statement of financial position, reports on a company's or individual's assets, liabilities, and owners equity at a given point in time.

Name: Financial Security Data
Description: A financial security represents an ownership (equity), debt agreement (bonds), or rights to ownership (derivatives) which can be marketed as a financial instrument.

Name: HSBC Financial Statement Data
Description: They are written records of HSBC 's financial situation. They include standard reports like the balance sheet, income or profit and loss statements, and cash flow statement

Name: Framework Data
Description: A framework that that organises and manages data by defining structures that provide classification categories to aid a business function.

Name: Geopolitical Entity Data
Description: A geopolitical area is a geographical area associated with some sort of political structure. With its governing body, a geopolitical entity acts as an agent with autonomy. It includes countries, states, city-states, and empires.

Name: Geospatial Location Data
Description: A contact address that is able to identify a position on the surface of the globe.

Name: HR Case Data
Description: Tickets or Cases raised by worker for HR support

Name: HSBC Business Framework Data
Description: Information describing the organisational and management structure of HSBC, examples of which are business and functional hierarchies, legal entities and geographic scope.

Name: HSBC Entity Data
Description: An organisational entity in which the HSBC group has a form of ownership or other financial interest which has to be reported on to the regulatory bodies which govern the activities of the group.

Name: Ledger Account Data
Description: A numerical representation of the net increases and decreases in an account at a specific point in time on specific asset or liability or equity.

Name: Identification Data
Description: The set of information that can only identify an individual on HSBC systems and processes.

Name: Individual Data
Description: A natural person that can be identified in which HSBC has a direct or indirect interest.

Name: Individual Financial Data
Description: Financial information pertaining to individuals (prospects or customers).

Name: Inferred Party Data
Description: A relationship we have derived based upon information we have with a party.

Name: Infrastructure Data
Description: IT Service related Configuration Item Name as recorded in CMDB and linked to an IT Service.

Name: Insurance Policy Data
Description: A contract between an insurer and policyholder(s) which details the terms and conditions of the insurance.

Name: Insured Object Data
Description: An asset insured under the terms and conditions of an insurance policy.

Name: Intellectual Property Data
Description: A broad categorical description for the set of intangibles owned and legally protected by a company from outside use or implementation without consent. Intellectual property can consist of trade secrets, copyrights and trademarks or simply ideas.

Name: Interest Rate Data
Description: It is the rate a bank or other lender charges to borrow its money, or the rate a bank pays its savers for keeping money in an account.

Name: IT Development KPI Data
Description: A financial or other target for an Entity which is considered key to the performance of IT development organisation.

Name: IT Service Data
Description: The IT service component type is used to define a GSD / PLADA Service. Definitions should therefore be viewed in those tools. In many cases an it service will have a one to one relationship with an application instance and effectively represent the same thing. The term service is used predominantly when referring to the infrastructure, resilience, availability, release and incident aspects of the deployed instance - commonly referred to as ITSM (IT Service Management). Whilst one to one relationships are most common, one to many relationships can exist in both directions owing to legacy definition practices and/or the technical/architectural complexity of the deployment.

Name: IT Service Management Data
Description:
ITSM (or IT Service Management) refers to all the activities involved in designing, creating, delivering, supporting 
and managing the lifecycle of IT services 

Incident
IT incident management is an area of IT service management (ITSM) wherein the IT team returns a service to normal as quickly as possible after a disruption, in a way that aims to create as little negative impact on the business as possible

Problem
Problem management is the set of processes and activities responsible for managing the lifecycle of all problems that could happen in an IT service. It's main goal is to prevent problems and their resulting incidents from happening

Change
IT Change management is the addition, modification or removal of any authorised, planned, or supported service or service component that could have an effect on IT services.

Name: Monitored Object Data
Description: Any instance, or group of instances of account entries, customer profiles, inter-customer relationships and their associated financial behaviour by way of transactions, payments and trades that are systematically reviewed following an alert during a compliance monitoring process

Name: Legal Document Data
Description: Written statement of facts and a proof or evidence of existence of a particular transaction between HSBC and Customer to be answerable/liable for satisfaction of the charges created therein.

Name: Legal Hierarchy Data
Description: Organisational hierarchies represent the relationships between the organisations that make up the particular business.

Name: Location Data
Description: A physical or virtual place where something can be found, a destination or a bounded area, about which HSBC wishes to keep information.

Name: Market Data
Description:
Publically available or commercially licensable research information about financial instruments or organisational financials and ratios from external data aggregators, such as:
* Standard descriptive and pricing data for a financial instrument
* Exchange rates and interest rates
* Total market volumes, volatility, and flows (off-HSBC data)

Name: Medical Record Data
Description: Information relating to the health and medical history of an individual.

Name: Metadata Data
Description: A set of data that describes and gives information about other data.

Name: Portfolio Data
Description: A grouping of financial assets such as stocks, bonds, commodities, currencies and cash equivalents, as well as their fund counterparts, including mutual, exchange-traded and closed funds.

Name: Operational Data
Description: An event that supports the execution of the activities of a business organisation.

Name: Operational KPI Data
Description: A financial or other target for an Entity which is considered key to the operational performance of an organisation.

Name: Organisational Financial Data
Description: Financial information pertaining to non-HSBC legal entities (prospects, customers or vendors), including liquidity risk information.

Name: Organisational Structure Data
Description: An organisational structure is a system that outlines how certain activities are directed in order to achieve the goals of HSBC. These activities can include rules, roles and responsibilities. The organisational structure also determines how information flows from level to level within the HSBC.

Name: Organisational Unit Data
Description: A Group of workers who are responsible for the delivery of business services based on a set of operating practices and who ensure compliance to the business rules set forth by a business policy.

Name: Organisation Data
Description: A party, usually consisting of a number of individuals or groups bound by common purposes and activities, that may stand alone in an operational or legal context.

Name: Organisation Registration Data
Description: Information in relation to the registration of an organisation with the Formation Authority that granted its formation.

Name: Other Related Party Data
Description: A role assumed by a given individual or organisation, with respect to another individual or organisation, to support or provide advice to a customer, but who sits outside that customer's management or ownership structure.

Name: Party Data
Description: A participant that may have contact with HSBC or that is of interest to HSBC.

Name: Payment Data
Description: A financial transaction where one form of good, service or financial asset is exchanged for another in proportions that have been previously agreed upon by all parties involved.

Name: Performance Data
Description: How well a person or worker or machine does work in specific period.

Name: Plant and Machinery Data
Description: Set of tangible moveable assets or resources for carrying on the business. An asset is not plant or machinery if it is stock in trade, the business premises or part of the business premises. Includes but is not limited to, location of assets, depreciation year and schedule.

Name: Retail Pool Data
Description: A group of retail credit exposures with similar characteristics for the purpose of risk-weighted asset calculation.

Name: Postal Address Data
Description: An address, recognised by the postal system, that can be used to communicate with, or locate a party or an asset of interest to HSBC.

Name: Pricing Data
Description: Pricing data and information relating to the value of a financial instrument.

Name: Product and Service Catalogue Data
Description: An organised and curated collection of any and all business and information technology related services that can be performed by, for, or within an enterprise.

Name: Product Application Data
Description: A formal request from a customer or a prospect to obtain a product from an HSBC business.

Name: Product Data
Description: Any goods or services that can be offered, sold or purchased by HSBC, its competitors and other parties during the normal course of business.

Name: Project Data
Description: An individual or collaborative enterprise that is carefully planned to achieve a particular aim.

Name: Prospect Data
Description: An individual or organisation that is not a customer but is considered a potential customer of HSBC through the marketing and sales process.

Name: Prospective Worker Data
Description: A prospective worker looking for employment with the organisation.

Name: Real Estate Data
Description: Real estate asset inventory information, including properties owned and leased, locations, square footage, physical HVAC equipment and names of property managers and management companies.

Name: Regulator Data
Description: A regulator is a person or organisation appointed by a government to control or regulate an area of activity such as banking or industry.

Name: Reinsurance Data
Description: Insurance Policies in line with terms of a reinsurance treaty, which cedes some of the risk to an external entity in exchange for a reinsurance premium

Name: Related Party Data
Description: A related party is a person or an entity that is related to the reporting entity, if that person has control, joint control, or significant influence over the entity or is a member of its key management personnel.

Name: Research Paper Data
Description: A substantial piece of academic writing, usually done as a requirement for a class, in which the author does independent research into a topic and writes a description of the findings of that research.

Name: Account Data
Description: A position keeping mechanism used to monitor both monetary and non-monetary standings.

Name: Risk Event Data
Description: Information used to determine risks associated with the possibility of loss resulting from inadequate or failed HSBC processes, people and systems or from external events, including legal risk.

Name: Risk Rating Data
Description: A measurement scale of accreditation created based on assessment of individual risk domains. This includes ratings created through Global and regional policies, as well as external ratings

Name: Shipment Data
Description: An amount of a particular kind of cargo that is sent to another country on a ship, train, aeroplane, or other vehicle.

Name: Social Media and News Feeds Data
Description: Websites and applications that enable users to create and share content or to participate in social networking.
L1 Domain Name: Social Media and News Feeds Data

Name: Software Data
Description: A set of computer programs, procedures or routines that have been designed to perform a specific function.

Name: Staff Policy Data
Description: Policies relavant to worker set by the organisation.

Name: Standard Terms and Conditions Data
Description: Set of rules and regulations for HSBC products and services

Name: Supplier Data
Description: A person or department that provides something needed such as a product or service to execute HSBC business.

Name: Trade Data
Description: A transfer of ownership of goods or cash flows from one party to another in exchange for money or another product or service.

Name: Trade Finance Instrument Data
Description: Trade finance (TF) is an important part of the transaction services offered by HSBC. It is a payment instrument and at the same time effectively manages the risks associated with doing business internationally.

Name: Transaction Data
Description: Information that identifies a transfer of cash, securities or financial instruments from a person, organisation or account to another.

Name: Vacation and Time-Off Data
Description: Time not spent in work, due to holiday entitlement, sick leave, and other reasons for absence.

Name: Valuation Data
Description: An estimation of the worth of something, especially one carried out by a professional valuer.

Name: Virtual Address Data
Description: A location that has no physical location.

Name: Watchlist Data
Description: A classification that defines entities of the same type that are of interest to HSBC for a specific purpose.

Name: Worker Data
Description: An individual that has a direct or indirect contract with HSBC to provide their services.

Name: Worker Profile Data
Description: Information pertaining to the biography (such as employment and financial history), anticipated transactional behaviour, social profile, non-demographic segmentation and lifecycle of a worker.
